io.servicetalk.transport.netty.internal

Class NettyConnection.TerminalPredicate<Read>

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.servicetalk.transport.netty.internal.NettyConnection.TerminalPredicate<Read>
  • Type Parameters:
    Read - Type of objects tested by this Predicate.
    All Implemented Interfaces:
    java.util.function.Predicate<Read>
    Enclosing interface:
    NettyConnection<Read,Write>

    public static final class NettyConnection.TerminalPredicate<Read>
extends java.lang.Object
implements java.util.function.Predicate<Read>
    A dynamic Predicate to detect terminal message in a stream as returned by NettyConnection.read(). Use replaceCurrent(Predicate) for replacing the current Predicate and discardIfCurrent(Predicate) to revert back to the original Predicate.

    If a dynamic predicate (as set by replaceCurrent(Predicate) terminates the stream, this will automatically revert to the original Predicate as done by calling discardIfCurrent(Predicate).
